==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Juicy
<hw>Jui"cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Juicier</adjf>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Juiciest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bounding with juice;
succulent.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Very profitable, or presenting the prospect of much
profit; <as>as, a <ex>juicy</ex> job; a <ex>juicy</ex> sales contract; a
<ex>juicy</ex> customer ripe for the plucking</as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Very interesting, especially due to scandalous or
salacious nature; -- of information; <as>as, <ex>juicy</ex>
gossip</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juise</ent>⟦br⟧
